      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): allow OpenAI OAuth for audio transcription",
        "body": "Closes #96135\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users with an OpenAI/Codex OAuth profile configured for `tools.media.audio` would lose batch audio transcription when OpenClaw routed OpenAI audio through `openai-audio-transcriptions`.\n\nThe failing path rejected the selected OAuth profile before dispatch with: `requires an OpenAI API key profile`.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`openai-audio-transcriptions` is now treated as an OpenAI bearer-auth API alongside `openai-chatgpt-responses`, so OAuth/token profiles can satisfy the shared model-auth guard for batch audio transcription. Direct OpenAI Platform model APIs such as `openai-responses` still require API-key auth.\n\nThe shared resolver now preserves shipped mixed-auth precedence for default/fallback profile resolution: if an OpenAI env API key such as `CODEX_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY` is available, audio transcription keeps the env API key ahead of a default OAuth profile. Explicit locked OAuth profiles still use OAuth for `openai-audio-transcriptions`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers who intentionally use OpenAI/Codex OAuth for voice-note or batch audio transcription can use their selected OpenAI OAuth profile again instead of being blocked before transcription runs.\n\nExisting mixed-auth users with an OpenAI OAuth default profile and an env API key keep API-key transcription behavior unless they explicitly lock the OAuth profile.\n\nUsers with OpenAI API keys are otherwise unaffected, and non-audio OpenAI Platform APIs remain API-key-only.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFocused tests:\n\n```bash\nenv OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_SCOPE=worktree node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts src/media-understanding/runner.local-no-auth.test.ts src/media-understanding/runner.auto-audio.test.ts\n# [test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 48.90s\n# media-understanding: 23 tests passed\n# agents: 74 tests passed\n```\n\nFormatting and diff checks:\n\n```bash\npnpm format:check -- src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts src/media-understanding/runner.local-no-auth.test.ts src/media-understanding/runner.auto-audio.test.ts\n# All matched files use the correct format.\n\ngit diff --check\n# clean\n```\n\nAutoreview:\n\n```bash\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n# autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\n# overall: patch is correct (0.82)\n```\n\nDependency/source evidence checked:\n\n- Official OpenAI OpenAPI spec from Stainless: global `ApiKeyAuth` is HTTP bearer auth, and `/audio/transcriptions` is the `createTranscription` endpoint.\n- Installed official `openai` Node SDK generated source: `audio.transcriptions.create()` posts to `/audio/transcriptions` with `__security: { bearerAuth: true }`; `client.ts` sends bearer auth as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.\n- The linked issue includes direct runtime evidence that an OpenAI OAuth credential successfully returned HTTP 200 from `POST /v1/audio/transcriptions` with `model=gpt-4o-mini-transcribe`, including a real uploaded voice-note case with API-key fallback disabled.\n\nLive after-fix proof:\n\n- A follow-up PR comment includes live OpenClaw CLI proof on `codex/fix-openai-oauth-transcription` at `7177136d859410c0f8b54c6d123bbab88b30ae2d` using `pnpm openclaw infer audio transcribe --model openai/gpt-4o-mini-transcribe --json`.\n- The proof ran with `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_OAUTH_TOKEN`, `OPENAI_BASE_URL`, and `OPENAI_AUDIO_BASE_URL` unset, using isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME=<tmp>` and `OPENCLAW_AUTH_STORE_READONLY=1`. No OpenClaw auth profile was persisted after the run.\n- The command returned `ok: true` with an `audio.transcription` output through the patched `openai-audio-transcriptions` path using OAuth-only credentials.\n- ClawSweeper re-review on June 27, 2026 at 17:20 UTC marked contributor proof sufficient. The later mixed OAuth-plus-API-key precedence finding has now been addressed in commit `241a743566`.\n",
        "branch": "codex/fix-openai-oauth-transcription",
